CAPE Submission Measure

USAGE:
    cape submission measure [OPTIONS] PATH
    cape submission measure --all

DESCRIPTION:
    Measure UPLC program(s) and generate metrics.json. This wrapper auto-discovers the
    scenario and cape-tests.json based on repository layout. No explicit scenario or test
    flags are supported here.

OPTIONS:
    -h, --help            Show this help message
    -a, --all             Measure all submissions under submissions/
        --no-color        Disable colored output
        --verbose         Verbose output

BEHAVIOR:
    - Scenario is inferred from the path: submissions/<scenario>/<submission>/...
    - Cape-tests.json is REQUIRED at scenarios/<scenario>/cape-tests.json
    - Test suite is passed to measure tool for comprehensive validation (-t)
    - metrics.json is created/updated alongside each .uplc file measured.

EXAMPLES:
    - Measure one submission folder:
        cape submission measure submissions/fibonacci/Plinth_1.52.0.0_User

    - Measure all submissions:
        cape submission measure --all
